Add 25 community/neighborhood test pages for popup address detection

Each page mirrors a different real-world real estate site pattern (Zillow,
Redfin, Realtor.com, Compass, Lennar, Toll Brothers, Howard Hughes, HOA
portals, broker neighborhood guides) and stresses a distinct address-embed
technique - H1/title/meta, JSON-LD, microdata, hCard, breadcrumbs, image
alt, canonical URL, og: tags, iframe src, data-* attributes, hidden tabs,
inline JSON blobs, footer-only, multiple-address tables, and landmark
red herrings. A test-index.html hub documents the expected address and
difficulty for each case, and the Neighborhoods dropdown is updated
across the site so QA can click through them sequentially.
